The present invention will become more fully understood from the detailed description given hereinbelow and the accompanying drawings which are given by way of illustration only, and thus, are not limitative of the present invention, and wherein:


FIG. 1 is a schematic diagram of a brake system for a motor vehicle, including a control apparatus according to one embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 2 is a diagram specifically showing the structure of a pressure control valve in the system;


FIG. 3 is a block diagram showing a procedure for controlling the turning behavior of a vehicle;


FIG. 4 is a diagram showing in detail a part of the procedure shown in FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 is a chart showing a pulse signal output from a command block in FIG. 4;


FIG. 6 is a diagram illustrating a function of the control apparatus performed when the vehicle tends to oversteer; FIG. 7 is a diagram illustrating a function of the control apparatus performed when the vehicle tends to understeer;


FIG. 8 is a diagram illustrating a function of the control apparatus performed in the case where, in the state shown in FIG. 6, the brake pedal is further depressed; and


FIG. 9 is a diagram illustrating a function of the control apparatus performed in the case where, in the state shown in FIG. 7, the brake pedal is further depressed.
